            {
              "text": "Frequently Asked Questions"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "tag": "h3",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "What are MRO products?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "MRO products are maintenance, repair, and operations supplies that support industrial business functions without becoming part of the final manufactured product."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "tag": "h3",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "What is included in industrial MRO?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Industrial MRO includes personal protective equipment, maintenance chemicals, tools, facility supplies, material handling equipment, electrical components, safety equipment, packaging supplies, HVAC systems, and office supplies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "tag": "h3",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Are PPE and adhesives considered MRO products?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Yes, both personal protective equipment and industrial adhesives are classified as MRO products since they support operations but don't become part of the final product."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "tag": "h3",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "How are MRO products different from OEM parts?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "OEM parts are original equipment manufacturer components designed specifically for particular machines, while MRO products are general supplies and consumables used across various equipment and operations."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
